Region-wide, the shift reduces daily VMT across all geography types — City Area and Medium District produce similar-sized reductions; Workshop Area's is somewhat smaller, consistent with it being the coarsest geography (fewer, larger areas mean some "shifted" trips were already relatively close by).

---

## VMT vs. VHD by County {#vmt-vs-vhd}

Each point is one county's change in daily VMT (x-axis) plotted against its change in VHD (y-axis), for whichever shift level, period, and geography type is selected below — a way to see whether delay reductions track driving reductions county by county, not just region-wide. Points in the lower-left quadrant (less VMT, less VHD) are the expected pattern; a county landing elsewhere would suggest its delay change is coming more from re-routing/assignment effects than from less driving overall.

